<div class="container">
    <h1>Hi Albee Account Deletion</h1>

    <p>
        Users may delete their Hi Albee account and all associated data at any time directly within the app.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Delete Your Account</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Open the Hi Albee app</li>
        <li>Go to <strong>Profile Settings</strong></li>
        <li>Tap <strong>“Delete Account and All Data”</strong></li>
        <li>Confirm your deletion request</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>What Data Is Deleted</h2>
    <p>
        When your account is deleted, the following data is permanently removed:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Account information (including email and user ID)</li>
        <li>Chat history and reflections</li>
        <li>Insights and reports</li>
        <li>Enneagram responses</li>
        <li>Preference and familiarity data</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        Account deletion is permanent and cannot be undone.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
        Some limited technical logs (such as anonymized server logs or crash logs) may be retained temporarily
        for security, fraud prevention, and system integrity purposes. These logs are automatically deleted
        within a limited retention period.
    </p>

    <h2>Need Assistance?</h2>
    <p>
        If you experience any issues deleting your account, please contact us at 
        <a href="mailto:support@hialbee.com">support@hialbee.com</a>.
    </p>
</div>

